Citation.sTitle: Vapor liquid equilibria for the ternary mixture of carbon dioxide + 1-propanol + propyl acetate at elevated pressures
Citation.sAbstract: Vapor liquid equilibrium (VLE) data for the ternary mixture of carbon dioxide, 1-propanol and propyl acetate were measured in this study at  308.2, 313.2, and 318.2 K, and at pressures ranging from 4 to 10MPa. A static type phase equilibrium apparatus with visual sapphire windows was  used in the experimental measurements. New VLE data for CO2 in the mixed solvent were presented. These ternary VLE data at elevated pressures  were also correlated using either the modified Soave Redlich Kwong or Peng Robinson equation of state (EOS), and by employing either the  van der Waals one-fluid or Huron Vidal mixing model. Satisfactory correlation results from both EOS models are reported with temperatureindependent  binary interaction parameters. It is observed that at 318.2K and 10MPa, 1-propanol may probably be separated from propyl acetate  into the vapor phase at the entire concentration range in the presence of high pressure CO2.
